task.summary: Example harmonic_repulsive_3d.py saves final state of simulation to disk.
Tweeked double loop force calculation, so the inner loop has it own force (a little faster).
Change set to list, so the autotune always test double loop before neighbour list.
Compute displacement directly (no function call) in cell list function.
Updated readme file, and descriptive example.
Added example with the Wahnström mixture (3D), and added functuallity in the Simulation class to support it.
Added short description to examples scripts
Add autogenerated list of examples to readme file
Autotuner test speed of double loop force calculations running on a single core
Added vectorised force calculations. The implimentation uses only NumPy, no Numba.
Bug fix. The vectorized force now uses converte an the sigma and epsilon funciton to arrays (only worked for constant functions before).
Example of two harmonic repulsive rods in 1D
Examples in readme file are now sorted.
Files for publishing first version (minor chages)
update link to examples to GitHub
Update requirements. Bugfix: SymPy was missing, SciPy is not needed).
autotuner printed even when it should be verbose
Update CHANGELOG.md to reflect that autotuner printed even when it should be verbose
Benchmark data for running standard system on SDU cluster
Enable that the package can be invoked from the commandline
